HEADWORD: Paresis
<hw>Par"e*sis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., from Gr.
<grk>pa`resis</grk>, fr. <grk>parie`nai</grk> to let go;
<grk>para`</grk> from + <grk>"ie`nai</grk> to send.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Incomplete paralysis, affecting motion but not
sensation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Parethmoid</ent>⟦br⟧
